FILE: library/meta/exploration-goal-design/choose-the-scenario-class-that-makes-a-narrow-hybrid-concrete.md
# Choose The Scenario Class That Makes A Narrow Hybrid Concrete

When a branch already survives only as a narrow hybrid, choose the scenario
class that makes that exact hybrid operationally testable.

Do not promote alternative geometries into co-primary status just because they
are also named in the chain. Keep at most one explicit comparator when it helps
test whether the survivor is genuinely specific or merely a relabeling of
generic geometry language.

In Step 3 Exploration 001 this kept `filament or tube concentration` primary
for the hybrid `direction coherence + tube persistence` and preserved
`sheet/pancake concentration` only as a robustness check.

Filed from:
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-003-exploration-001.md`
FILE: library/meta/workflow-monitoring/do-not-treat-initial-report-summary-scaffolds-as-completion-sentinels.md
# Do Not Treat Initial Report Summary Scaffolds As Completion Sentinels

Explorer-session monitoring should not rely on sentinel-file existence alone
when the session writes `REPORT-SUMMARY.md` as an initial scaffold.

A summary file can appear before the substantive report is complete, so a
workflow should distinguish between "artifact created" and "usable findings are
present." Otherwise session state can look complete while the actual report is
still pending or only partially written.

Filed from:
- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-003-exploration-001.md`

